---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Me | Chayse Lavallais"
  description="About my work as a chemical engineer and sustainability scientist focused on LCA and product carbon footprints."
>
  <section class="subpage-hero wide-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">About Me</p>
    <h1>Technical sustainability methods for real-world decisions.</h1>
    <p class="intro">
      I am a chemical engineer and sustainability scientist working at the
      intersection of sustainability, technology, and business, where
      quantitative analysis can help organizations make better decisions in the
      face of complex environmental and economic tradeoffs.
    </p>
    <p class="intro">
      I am particularly interested in developing methodologies and
      decision-support frameworks that transform technical data into practical
      insights for engineers, researchers, and business leaders. That interest
      has shaped my career across both industry and academia, leading me to work
      on problems ranging from refinery process optimization to life cycle
      assessment, product carbon footprints, carbon accounting, and emerging
      sustainability technologies. Regardless of the application, my work is
      driven by a common objective: developing rigorous, transparent, and
      practical approaches for evaluating technologies and supporting more
      informed decision-making.
    </p>
    <p class="intro">
      Outside of work, I enjoy traveling and exploring how place, culture, and
      lived experience shape the way people understand success, opportunity,
      and belonging. This interest connects to my TEDx talk on growing up as a
      third-culture kid and how that experience shaped my understanding of
      success:
      <a
        class="text-link"
        href="https://www.ted.com/talks/chayse_lavallais_knowing_success"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noreferrer"
      >
        Watch “Knowing Success”
      </a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <h2>Core Expertise</h2>
      <p>
        My work centers on methods that make environmental assessment more
        transparent, consistent, and useful for technical and strategic
        decisions.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-grid two reveal-grid">
      <article tabindex="0">
        <h2>Life Cycle Assessment</h2>
        <span class="reveal-cue">Learn more</span>
        <p>
          Environmental assessment of chemical products, emerging technologies,
          and industrial systems across life cycle stages.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article tabindex="0">
        <h2>Circular Economy</h2>
        <span class="reveal-cue">Learn more</span>
        <p>
          Assessment of circular resource pathways, recovered products, and
          systems that turn waste streams into useful materials and lower-impact
          products.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article tabindex="0">
        <h2>Techno-Economic Analysis</h2>
        <span class="reveal-cue">Learn more</span>
        <p>
          Evaluation of early-stage technologies through process, cost,
          scale-up, and commercialization considerations.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article tabindex="0">
        <h2>Decision Analysis</h2>
        <span class="reveal-cue">Learn more</span>
        <p>
          Uncertainty analysis, Monte Carlo simulation, and
          multi-criteria decision frameworks for sustainability problems.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <h2>Industry Experience</h2>
      <p>
        My sustainability assessment work spans research and industry contexts
        where chemical systems, resource recovery, and emissions accounting
        intersect.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-grid reveal-grid">
      <article tabindex="0">
        <h2>Chemicals and Materials</h2>
        <span class="reveal-cue">Learn more</span>
        <p>
          Product-level sustainability assessment for chemical products,
          manufacturing pathways, and emerging lower-carbon technologies.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article tabindex="0">
        <h2>Wastewater and Resource Recovery</h2>
        <span class="reveal-cue">Learn more</span>
        <p>
          Evaluation of technologies that recover nutrients, reduce emissions,
          and create value from wastewater and waste nitrogen streams.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article tabindex="0">
        <h2>Refining and Process Operations</h2>
        <span class="reveal-cue">Learn more</span>
        <p>
          Process engineering experience with hydroprocessing, refinery
          operations, process optimization, and industrial constraints.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article tabindex="0">
        <h2>Bio-Based Feedstocks</h2>
        <span class="reveal-cue">Learn more</span>
        <p>
          Evaluation of renewable and alternative feedstock pathways, including
          how feedstock choices influence carbon footprints and sustainability
          tradeoffs.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article tabindex="0">
        <h2>Circular Economy</h2>
        <span class="reveal-cue">Learn more</span>
        <p>
          Assessment of circular resource pathways, recovered products, and
          metrics for comparing environmental and economic tradeoffs.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article tabindex="0">
        <h2>Emerging Technologies</h2>
        <span class="reveal-cue">Learn more</span>
        <p>
          Early-stage evaluation of technologies where performance, cost,
          uncertainty, and sustainability outcomes need to be assessed together.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
